{"id": 239770754, "title": "Portugal cruises into Euro 2024 knockout stages as Belgium bounces back", "text": "Dortmund, Germany - Portugal outclassed Turkey to secure a place in the last 16 of Euro 2024 with a 3-0 win in Dortmund on Saturday, while Belgium kept its hopes alive with a 2-0 victory over Romania.Cristiano Ronaldo's Portuguese side, European champions in 2016, is among the favorites to win the title in Germany and the team lived up to its status with a comprehensive victory in front of a partisan crowd to secure first place in Group F.Bernardo Silva of Manchester City opened the scoring midway through the first half, sweeping the ball home after a low Nuno Mendes cross was deflected into his path.", "summary": "Cristiano Ronaldo's Portuguese side is among the favorites to win the title in Germany and the team lived up to its status against Turkey.", "url": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2024/06/23/soccer/portugal-cruises-turkey/", "image": "https://www.japantimes.co.jp/japantimes/uploads/images/2024/06/23/404933.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-23 01:49:00", "author": "Andy Scott,Web Master", "authors": ["Andy Scott", "Web Master"], "language": "en", "catgory": "sports", "source_country": "jp", "sentiment": 0.483}